body.pre:
The AMPA Metabolic Pathway Simulator is an amalgamation of four distinct models, which combined aim to provide a maximalist model of the postsynaptic spine environment.
The models are:
Hayer and Bhalla (2005) - AMPAR dynamics and CaMKII switch Iyengar and Bhalla (1999) - mGluR pathway Jain (2009) - mTOR pathway and protein tranlsation (generic) Rao Padala et al (2017) - Wnt signalling pathway
This version features a persistent background of glutamate from the synaptic cleft to simulate persistent firing.
Details of each model can be found under the Annotations tab on this page in Copasi. The Hayer and Bhalla model originated from BioModels Database: A Database of Annotated Published Models (http://www.ebi.ac.uk/biomodels/). It is copyright (c) 2005-2011 The BioModels.net Team. It is a modified version generated by Richard Fitzpatrick

Main compartment of model. Includes majority of reacting molecules. Represents a small spine head in the hippocampal region of the brain.
Compartment to represent postsynaptic density. Useful for future MAGUK interactions and translocational reactions.
Stimulus pool for various species in the model. Allows for artifical influx (or efflux) when necessary during investigations.
Artificial compartment for radioactive labelling info. Legacy from Jain model.
Artificial compartment for basal translation info. Legacy from Jain model.
